{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findInstall?\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">findInstall?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.ElanInstall\">ElanInstall</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LeanInstall\">LeanInstall</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LakeInstall\">LakeInstall</a></span>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Attempt to automatically detect an Elan, Lake, and Lean installation.\n\nFirst, it calls `findElanInstall?` to detect a Elan installation.\nThen it attempts to detect if Lake and Lean are part of a single installation\nwhere the `lake` executable is co-located with the `lean` executable (i.e., they\nare in the same directory). If Lean and Lake are not co-located, Lake will\nattempt  to find the their installations separately by calling\n`findLeanInstall?` and `findLakeInstall?`. Setting `LAKE_OVERRIDE_LEAN` to true\nwill force Lake to use `findLeanInstall?` even if co-located.\n\nWhen co-located, Lake will assume that Lean and Lake's binaries are located in\n`<sysroot>/bin`, their Lean libraries  in `<sysroot>/lib/lean`, Lean's source files\nin `<sysroot>/src/lean`, and Lake's source files in `<sysroot>/src/lean/lake`,\nfollowing the pattern of a regular Lean toolchain.\n","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findInstall?","kind":"def","line":363,"name":"Lake.findInstall?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L363-L390"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findLakeInstall?\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">findLakeInstall?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LakeInstall\">LakeInstall</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Attempt to detect Lake's installation by first checking the `lakeBuildHome?`\nof the running executable, then trying the `LAKE_HOME` environment variable.\n\nIt assumes that the Lake installation is organized the same way it is built.\nThat is, with its binary located at `<lake-home>/.lake/build/bin/lake` and its\nstatic library and `.olean` files in `<lake-home>/.lake/build/lib`, and\nits source files located directly in `<lake-home>`.\n","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findLakeInstall?","kind":"def","line":346,"name":"Lake.findLakeInstall?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L346-L361"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findLeanInstall?\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">findLeanInstall?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LeanInstall\">LeanInstall</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Attempt to detect Lean's installation by using the `LEAN` and `LEAN_SYSROOT`\nenvironment variables.\n\nIf `LEAN_SYSROOT` is set, use it. Otherwise, check `LEAN` for the `lean`\nexecutable. If `LEAN` is set but empty, Lean will be considered disabled.\nOtherwise, Lean's location will be determined by trying `findLeanSysroot?`\nusing value of `LEAN` or, if unset, the `lean` in `PATH`.\n\nSee `LeanInstall.get` for how it assumes the Lean install is organized.\n","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findLeanInstall?","kind":"def","line":320,"name":"Lake.findLeanInstall?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L320-L344"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.getLakeInstall?\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">getLakeInstall?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">lake</span> : <a href=\"./Init/System/FilePath.html#System.FilePath\">System.FilePath</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LakeInstall\">LakeInstall</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Heuristically validate that `getLakeBuildHome?` is a proper Lake installation\nby check for `Lake.olean` in the installation's `lib` directory.\n","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.getLakeInstall?","kind":"def","line":309,"name":"Lake.getLakeInstall?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L309-L318"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.lakeBuildHome?\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">lakeBuildHome?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">lake</span> : <a href=\"./Init/System/FilePath.html#System.FilePath\">System.FilePath</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/System/FilePath.html#System.FilePath\">System.FilePath</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Get the root of Lake's installation by assuming the executable\nis located at `<lake-home>/.lake/build/bin/lake`.\n","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.lakeBuildHome?","kind":"def","line":302,"name":"Lake.lakeBuildHome?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L302-L307"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findLakeLeanJointHome?\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">findLakeLeanJointHome?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/System/FilePath.html#System.FilePath\">System.FilePath</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Check if the running Lake's executable is co-located with Lean, and, if so,\ntry to return their joint home by assuming they are both located at `<home>/bin`.\n","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findLakeLeanJointHome?","kind":"def","line":290,"name":"Lake.findLakeLeanJointHome?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L290-L300"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findLeanCmdInstall?\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">findLeanCmdInstall?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">lean</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a> := <span class=\"fn\">&quot;lean&quot;</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LeanInstall\">LeanInstall</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Attempt to detect the installation of the given `lean` command\nby calling `findLeanSysroot?`. See `LeanInstall.get` for how it assumes the\nLean install is organized.\n","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findLeanCmdInstall?","kind":"def","line":282,"name":"Lake.findLeanCmdInstall?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L282-L288"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LeanInstall.get\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">LeanInstall</span>.<span class=\"name\">get</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">sysroot</span> : <a href=\"./Init/System/FilePath.html#System.FilePath\">System.FilePath</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">collocated</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool.false\">false</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LeanInstall\">LeanInstall</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Construct the `LeanInstall` object for the given Lean sysroot.\n\nDoes the following:\n1. Find `lean`'s githash.\n2. Finds the  `ar` and `cc` to use with Lean.\n3. Computes the sub-paths of the Lean install.\n\nFor (1), If `lake` is not-collocated with `lean`, invoke `lean --githash`;\notherwise, use Lake's `Lean.githash`. If the invocation fails, `githash` is\nset to the empty string.\n\nFor (2), if `LEAN_AR` or `LEAN_CC` are defined, it uses those paths.\nOtherwise, if Lean is packaged with an `llvm-ar` and/or `clang`, use them.\nIf not, use the `ar` and/or `cc` from the `AR` / `CC` environment variables\nor the system's `PATH`. This last step is needed because internal builds of\nLean do not bundle these tools (unlike user-facing releases).\n\nWe also track whether `LEAN_CC` was set to determine whether it should\nbe set in the future for `lake env`. This is because if `LEAN_CC` was not set,\nit needs to remain not set for `leanc` to work.\nEven setting it to the bundled compiler will break `leanc` -- see\n[leanprover/lean4#1281](https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/issues/1281).\n\nFor (3), it assumes that the Lean installation is organized the normal way.\nThat is, with its binaries located in `<lean-sysroot>/bin`, its\nLean libraries in `<lean-sysroot>/lib/lean`, and its system libraries in\n`<lean-sysroot>/lib`.\n","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LeanInstall.get","kind":"def","line":203,"name":"Lake.LeanInstall.get","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L203-L280"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findLeanSysroot?\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">findLeanSysroot?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">lean</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a> := <span class=\"fn\">&quot;lean&quot;</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/System/FilePath.html#System.FilePath\">System.FilePath</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Attempt to find the sysroot of the given `lean` command (if it exists)\nby calling `lean --print-prefix` and returning the path it prints.\nDefaults to trying the `lean` in `PATH`.\n","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findLeanSysroot?","kind":"def","line":186,"name":"Lake.findLeanSysroot?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L186-L201"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findElanInstall?\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">findElanInstall?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.ElanInstall\">ElanInstall</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Attempt to detect an Elan installation by checking the `ELAN` and `ELAN_HOME`\nenvironment variables. If `ELAN` is set but empty, Elan is considered disabled.\n","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.findElanInstall?","kind":"def","line":173,"name":"Lake.findElanInstall?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L173-L184"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LakeInstall.ofLean\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">LakeInstall</span>.<span class=\"name\">ofLean</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">lean</span> : <a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LeanInstall\">LeanInstall</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LakeInstall\">LakeInstall</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Construct a Lake installation co-located with the specified Lean installation. ","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LakeInstall.ofLean","kind":"def","line":159,"name":"Lake.LakeInstall.ofLean","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L159-L169"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LakeInstall.sharedLib\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">LakeInstall</span>.<span class=\"name\">sharedLib</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LakeInstall\">LakeInstall</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/System/FilePath.html#System.FilePath\">System.FilePath</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LakeInstall.sharedLib","kind":"def","line":156,"name":"Lake.LakeInstall.sharedLib","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L156-L157"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.instReprLakeInstall\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">instReprLakeInstall</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Repr.html#Repr\">Repr</a> <a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LakeInstall\">LakeInstall</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.instReprLakeInstall","kind":"instance","line":154,"name":"Lake.instReprLakeInstall","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L154-L154"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.instReprLakeInstall.repr\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">instReprLakeInstall</span>.<span class=\"name\">repr</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.LakeInstall\">LakeInstall</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Format/Basic.html#Std.Format\">Std.Format</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.instReprLakeInstall.repr","kind":"def","line":154,"name":"Lake.instReprLakeInstall.repr","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/lake/Lake/Config/InstallPath.lean#L154-L154"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/InstallPath.html#Lake.instInhabitedLakeInsta